      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EASY ACES (4) flew the lids with a fast early split and went on to clock 17.12 when a nose winner over 300m at Murray Bridge Straight. Has good box speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Can continue the winning form. ELEGANT FLINT (2) was midfield throughout and finished there last time when 5th (20.33) at Murray Bridge Straight. Solid record here at the distance winning three races. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Has ability and can measure up. EQUIVOCAL (5) broke from this box and proved too strong when a 1.75 lengths winner in fast time (22.87) in a TG1-4W at Gawler. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. VICTA SPENCER (7) is worth consideration.",
